"Byun H.-R., Tanaka H.L., Michalopoulou H., Pandey R.P., Azzaya D.","A study on ice control for the production of 5th-generation water resources and the arrest of global warming",2008,"Asia-Pacific Journal of Atmospheric Sciences","44","2",,"137","147",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-44949172632&partnerID=40&md5=edd8035398f96f81e0a3d4fd9ff7c9f3","Dept. of Environmental Atmospheric Sciences, Pukyong National Univ., Daeyeon-3 dong, Namku, Busan 608-737, South Korea; Center for Computational Sciences, University of Tsukuba, Tsukuba 305-8577, Japan; Division of Applied Physics, University of Athens, Building Phys-5, Athens 15784, Greece; National Institute of Hydrology, Roorkee-247 667 Uttaranchal, India; Institute of Meteorology and Hydrology, Juulchny udamj-5, Ulaanbaatar-46 21060, Mongolia","Byun, H.-R., Dept. of Environmental Atmospheric Sciences, Pukyong National Univ., Daeyeon-3 dong, Namku, Busan 608-737, South Korea; Tanaka, H.L., Center for Computational Sciences, University of Tsukuba, Tsukuba 305-8577, Japan; Michalopoulou, H., Division of Applied Physics, University of Athens, Building Phys-5, Athens 15784, Greece; Pandey, R.P., National Institute of Hydrology, Roorkee-247 667 Uttaranchal, India; Azzaya, D., Institute of Meteorology and Hydrology, Juulchny udamj-5, Ulaanbaatar-46 21060, Mongolia","After a lengthy investigation on the unnatural phenomena of ice, such as the formation of ice valleys, ice caves, and ice spikes, it was found that ice will play a very important role in the next generation. It is suggested in this study that natural evaporation can be reduced, that the condensation of water vapor can be promoted, and that a tremendous amount of betterquality water can be generated for future use through the artificial control of ice. It was likewise found that ice that has been increased through ice control reflects more insolation and can suppress global warming. When applied to the central part of Korea, ice control can prevent 614 mm of water from evaporating for eight months, without refrigerating energy. The amount of water that can be prevented from evaporating will reach 438 million tons when applied to Daechung Dam, which has a water surface of 73 km2 and many streams. Furthermore, by using 1 ton of continuously supplied ice, water vapor can be condensed into water resources at a rate of 37,440 g h-1 in 15°C air and 0.5 m s-1 wind. It is also calculated that 4.8 × 106 km2 of additional ice cover can terminate the global warming process. Ice control procedures involving the forced thickening of ice and delayed thawing are introduced herein. The related thermodynamics, simple experiments that were conducted, and observed results are reviewed briefly. To date, no harmful side effects of the use of ice control have been documented.","Evaporation; Global warming; Ice control; Water resources",,,,,,,"Bouchet, R. J., 1963: Evapotranspiration réelle evapotranspiration potentielle, Signification climatique, Int. Assoc. Sci. Hydrol., Berkeley, Calif., Symp. Publ. 62, 134-142Briggs, A., Sabaratnam, S., Condensation of steam in the presence of air on a single tube and a tube bank (2003) Int. J. Energy Res, 18, pp. 301-314; Brikowski, T., Anderson, W., Droughts & Reservoirs: Finding storage space underground (2006) Science Daily, , September 18; Byun, H.R., Tanaka, H.L., Observations and Inductions on the meteorological mysteries in the Ice Valley, Miryang, Korea (2007) J. Glaciol, , submitted to; Byun, H.R., Study on the mechanism of the Summer-time icing on the Ice-Valley (2006) Miryang City Korea, , 402pp, In Korean; Byun, H.R., Kim, K.H., Choi, K.S., Tanaka, H.L., The characteristics and thermal mechanism of the warm wind hole fond at the Ice valley in Mt. Jaeyak (2004) J. Korean Meteor. Soc, 40, pp. 453-465. , In Korean with English abstract; Byun, H.R., Seo, D.I., Lim, B.H., The observation of the naturally formed ice spikes and their inductive inferences (2004) J. Korean Meteor. Soc,