ay, E., Role of sea surface temperature and soil-moisture feedback in the 1998 Oklahoma-Texas drought (2000) Nature, 408, pp. 842-844; Hood, E., Williams, M., Clime, D., Sublimation from a seasonal snow pack at a continental, mid-latitude alpine site (1999) Hydrol. Process, 13, pp. 1781-1797; Hurtley, S., Szuromi, P., Ice sheet stability (2006) Science, 311, pp. 1669-1671; Hwang, S.J., Seo, K.S., Lee, S.H., Study on ice formation mechanism at the Ice Valley in Milyang Korea (2005) J. Korean Meteor. Soc, 41, pp. 29-40. , In Korean with English abstract; Kim, S.S., On the summertime freezing in the ice valley (Miryang) (1968) J. Korean Meteor. Soc, 4, pp. 13-18. , In Korean with English abstract; Lim, J.H., Byun, H.R., Characteristics of the development of the Okhotsk high and its relation to the atmospheric circulation over East Asia (2000) J. Korean Meteor. Soc, 36, pp. 507-518. , In Korean with English abstract; Lindzen, R. S., and A. P. Sloan, 1997: Statement concerning global warming presented to the Senate Committee on Environmental and Public Works. June 10, 1997. Massachusetts Institute of TechnologyLiu, J., Zhang, Z., Inoue, J., Horton, R.M., Evaluation of snow/ ice albedo parameterizations and their impacts on sea ice simulation (2007) Int. J. Climatol, 27, pp. 91-91; Lukovich, J.V., Barber, D.G., (2005) On the relative contributions of dynamic and thermodynamic forcing of sea ice concentration anomalies in the Southern Beaufort Sea inferred through spatio-temporal statistical analysis, , Center of Earth Observation Science, University of Manitoba Canada; Morse, B., Hicks, F., Advances in river ice hydrology 1999-2003 (2005) Hydro. Process, 19, pp. 247-263; Ohmura, A., Wild, M., Is the hydrological cycle accelerating? (2002) Science, 298, pp. 1345-1346; Oki, T., Kanae, S., Global hydrological cycles and world water resources (2006) Science, 313, pp. 1068-1072; Penman, H.L., Natural evaporation from open water, bare soil and grass (1948) Proc. Roy. Soc. Londo